text: Celeste Ferraris (born 29 September 1970) is a former synchronized swimmer from Australia. She competed in the women's solo and women's duet competitions at the . In 2020, Celeste was awarded a Faculty Medal from the Faculty of Science at the University of Newcastle, Australia, for her Honours research in Food Science and Human Nutrition. == References == Category:1970 births Category:Living people Category:Australian synchronised swimmers Category:Olympic synchronised swimmers of Australia Category:Synchronized swimmers at the 1992 Summer Olympics Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in synchronised swimming Category:Commonwealth Games bronze medallists for Australia
